behav_list = ['behavioral_antiviral_meds', 'behavioral_avoidance','behavioral_face_mask', 'behavioral_wash_hands',
       'behavioral_large_gatherings', 'behavioral_outside_home','behavioral_touch_face']
    
#from above correlation table we can see that behavioral attribute are correlated with h1n1_concern
#hence all the instances where participants was very concerned about h1n1, we fill 1 for all the behavioral attribute, 
#in ordert to fill na

for col in behav_list:
    train_merge.loc[(train_merge.h1n1_concern==3)&(train[col].isna()),col] = 1

#similary if all the value for behaviour is 1 then they are concerned
train_merge.loc[train_merge[behav_list].replace({1.0:True,0.0:False}).all(axis=1),'h1n1_concern'] = 3

#rest of the value lets fill in as 0 for behavioral attribute
train_merge[behav_list] = train_merge[behav_list].fillna(0)
train_merge['h1n1_concern'] = train_merge['h1n1_concern'].fillna(0)
In [14]:
def bar_prcntg(col_list_temp,label_dic = False,x_label=False):
    col_list = col_list_temp*2
    if(len(np.unique(col_list))==1):
        fig,axes = plt.subplots(2,1,figsize=(15,8),sharex=True)
    else:
        fig,axes = plt.subplots(2,2,figsize=(15,8),sharex=True)
   

    axes= axes.ravel()
    
    for ind in range(len(col_list)):

        if (ind < len(col_list)/2):
            #train_merge.groupby(col_list[ind]).respondent_id.value_counts(normalize=True).\
            #plot(kind='bar',ax = axes[ind],color='C0',legend=False)
            rect = (train_merge[col_list[ind]].value_counts(normalize=True).sort_index().round(2)*100).\
            plot(kind='bar',ax = axes[ind],color='C0',legend=False)
            axes[ind].set_ylabel('percentage')
            for patch in rect.patches:
                axes[ind].text(patch.get_x()+patch.get_width()/2,patch.get_y()+patch.get_height()/2,\
             str(round(patch.get_height()))+str('%'),ha = 'center', va='bottom',size=13)
               
   
        else:
            temp_cal = train_merge.groupby([col_list[ind],'h1n1_vaccine']).respondent_id.count()
            rect = round((temp_cal/temp_cal.groupby(level=0).sum())*100,2).unstack().\
            plot(kind='bar',stacked=True,legend=False,ax = axes[ind],color=['crimson','g'])
            axes[ind].set_ylabel('percentage')
            if(len(col_list)==2):
                axes[ind].set_title('Percentage of H1N1 vaccine response across each level',va = 'center', y=1.02,pad=2)
            if(label_dic):
                axes[ind].set_xticklabels(list(label_dic.values()))
            axes[ind].tick_params(rotation=0)
            if(x_label):
                axes[ind].set_xlabel(x_label[ind-2])
            
            for patch in rect.patches:
                axes[ind].text(patch.get_x()+patch.get_width()/2,patch.get_y()+patch.get_height()/2,\
                         str(round(patch.get_height()))+str('%'),ha = 'center', va='bottom',size=13)
   
    axes[ind].legend(['No','Yes'],loc='upper left',bbox_to_anchor=(1,1),title='H1N1 vaccine response')
    fig.suptitle('Count of '+ ' & '.join(col_list_temp) +' level',va='center',y=1.002)
    fig.tight_layout()

#rest of the value filled - allens - 
# fill these NAs with did not report DNR
others = ['education', 'income_poverty', 'marital_status', 'rent_or_own', 'employment_status']

for i in others:
    train_merge.loc[:, i] = train_merge.loc[:, i].replace(np.nan, 'DNR')

# columns with binary data with mode
binary = ['chronic_med_condition', 'child_under_6_months', 'health_worker','h1n1_knowledge']

for i in binary:
    train_merge.loc[:, i] = train_merge.loc[:, i].replace(np.nan, statistics.mode(train_merge.loc[:,i]))

mapping = {'age_group': {'18 - 34 Years': 0, '35 - 44 Years':1, '45 - 54 Years':2, '55 - 64 Years':3, '65+ Years':4},
          'education': {'DNR': 0, '< 12 Years': 1, '12 Years': 2, 'Some College': 3, 'College Graduate': 4},
          'race': {'Black': 0, 'Hispanic': 1, 'Other or Multiple': 2, 'White': 3},
          'sex': {'Female': 0, 'Male': 1},
          'income_poverty': {'DNR': 0, 'Below Poverty': 1, '<= $75,000, Above Poverty': 2, '> $75,000': 3},
          'marital_status': {'DNR': 0, 'Not Married': 1, 'Married': 2},
          'rent_or_own': {'DNR': 0, 'Own': 1, 'Rent': 2},
          'employment_status': {'DNR': 0, 'Not in Labor Force': 1, 'Unemployed': 2, 'Employed': 3},
          'census_msa': {'Non-MSA': 0, 'MSA, Not Principle  City': 1, 'MSA, Principle City': 2}}

tp=0; fp =0; fn = 0; tn = 0;
for i in range(len(hi_test.health_insurance)):
    if hi_test.health_insurance.iloc[i] == 1 and predicted[i] == 1:
        tp += 1
    if hi_test.health_insurance.iloc[i] == 1 and predicted[i] == 0:
        fp += 1
    if hi_test.health_insurance.iloc[i] == 0 and predicted[i] == 1:
        fn += 1
    if hi_test.health_insurance.iloc[i] == 0 and predicted[i] == 0:
        tn += 1
        
accuracy = (tp+tn)/len(predicted)
print(tp, fp, fn, tn)
print(accuracy)
